  "texts": [
    "This condition can be easily satisfied by adopting a smooth approximation of (3).",
    "B. Interaction strength adaptationWe complement the Reinforcement Learning agent with an interaction strength compensation to improve performance.",
    "We can exploit this additional degree of freedom to mitigate the limitations imposed by the small number of herders.",
    "Specifically, recalling that the strength of the interaction between herders and targets in Equation ( 4) can be modulated through the gain K(t), we employ a heuristic gradient-descent compensation lawK(t) = -α ∇ K ρ T,ss (x; H(t)) -ρ T (x) L 2, (12)with initial gain K(0) = 1.",
    "Such compensation law allows the convergence of the interaction strength gain to a value that locally minimizes the target distribution mismatch.IV."
